PRIVACY POLICY
Privacy Policy for SnapShot
1. Introduction
Welcome to SnapShot. We value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you use our app.
2. Information We Collect
a. Personal Information:
We may collect personal information that you provide to us directly, such as your name, email address, and any other information you choose to provide.
b. Non-Personal Information:
We collect non-personal information about your use of the app. This includes device information, app usage data, and other diagnostic data.
c. Photos and Media:
To provide our services, we may access photos and media on your device. We do not store or share these files.
3. Permissions We Require
SnapShot requires the following permissions to function correctly:
Storage: To read and save edited photos.
Camera: To capture photos directly within the app.
Internet: To serve advertisements and allow in-app purchases.
4. Use of Collected Information
a. To Provide and Maintain Our Service:
We use your information to deliver the services you request, such as editing photos and saving your work.
b. To Improve Our Services:
We analyze usage data to improve the functionality and user experience of our app.
Google Analytics & Firebase & Admob (Google); Googleâ€™s privacy policy is available
